Class CoreInterface

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
ICapsuleMonitor
public class CoreInterface
extends java.lang.Object
implements ICapsuleMonitor

API singleton for the core of KeYTestGen.

Instances of this class provide a single interface between backend modules and KeYTestGen itself, allowing them to request services related to test case generation.

Backend modules should not be allowed to interact with KeYTestGen2 through any other means than this singleton. TODO: Enforce this through access restriction.

Author:
christopher

public java.util.List<TestSuite> createTestSuites(java.io.File source,

                                                  boolean includeNative,
                                                  java.util.List<java.lang.String> methods)
                                           throws CoreException
Generate a set of test suites for a selection of methods in a Java source file. The test suites will will be in accord with the code coverage criteria specified.

Parameters:
source - path to the Java source file.
codeCoverageParser - code coverage critera to be satisfied by the generated test cases. May be null, in which case a default statement coverage is used. See ICodeCoverageParser.
Returns:
a test suite for the target class, in the specified test framework.
Throws:
TestGeneratorException - in the event that something went wrong in the process of test case generation.
CoreException
